properties.notes: This site was difficult to reach because the back alcove is a good foot higher than the mainstem due to wood and mud berms. We tried to drag our canoes to the upper site, but the water was not deep enough to float them, and the mud was too thick to walk. The big questions include: how far back into the alcove does this YFH go, and did it originate from the mainstream or somewhere in the alcove or an upstream tributary? Another  survey well back into the alcove is suggested for next spring/summer when the water level is higher.
